1. Installed Polybar-themes
	- lone https://github.com/adi1090x/polybar-themes.git
	- exec ~/.config/polybar/setup.sh --themes to switch 
	

2. Edit Kitty config to fit nord theme
	/home/cyph/.config/kitty/kitty.conf
		- change backround/foreground hex code 

3. Configure betterlockscreen
	cmd: <betterlockscreen -u Desktop/Stuff/nord2 --blur 0.5> (updates the wallpaper and adds a ?blur)

4. Configure picom
	/home/.cofig/picom/picom.conf
	- added opacity rule in 'picom.conf' - kitty terminal 

5. Configure spicetify
	/home/cyph4/.config/spicetify
	- cloned: https://github.com/morpheusthewhite/spicetify-themes.git (themes)
	- switch themes using <spicetify config current_theme THEME_NAME> (theme name located in /home/cyph4/.config/spicetify/Themes)






usefull tools

: xprop
	- get name of a program inorder to add make keybinds for it in configruation 

: ncdu 
	- storage cleanup 

: du -sh <dir>
	- how much storage space does a directory use up? 